 color=#628CBC>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#004088 class=headings><font color=#628CBC>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughtersofmalaeliu>DaughtersOfMalaeliu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Penny Priddy</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/20/02 4:04:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan/women.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fall of Malaehi- Past</span><hr size=1> ... a journey back in time, begins.<br>
<br>
The Mission<br>
<br>
Standing at attention, not daring to move a muscle, nor blink, the gangly, young Malaehi stares straight across the room of the Ancients. Her Elders have put her through rigorous trials, testing her enchanting abilities, sending her on quests spanning the entire planet of Norrath. On the marble table before her lies the items she has acquired for the Consul, proving she is strong and worthy.<br>
<br>
A ghostly pale Koada'dal femme, hair the same hue of white as her skin, peruses the items with distain. She spits: &quot;You troublesome little guttersnipe, you dare come back into our presence?! You think these paultry items deem you worthy to be one of us?! Tell me, how can a castaway orphan be of any use to the Ancients of Erollisi?&quot;<br>
<br>
Keeping her eyes glued to the tapestry on the far wall, Malaehi answers: &quot;I am pure of heart and chaste of body. Tis my sole purpose to serve the Goddess and the Consul, Mistress Kiae.&quot; Malaehi's eyes glaze over breifly, knowing what is to come. An earsplitting spell is cast and the breath is ripped from her lungs, suffocating her for a few agonizing minutes. Before her eyes disappear into the back of her head, the Elder releases her spell, dropping Mala to her knees, gasping for air. <br>
<br>
The Elder laughs derisively making the parting shot, before she exits: &quot;I, a mere Enchantress, can do this, she will crumble in the face of a Necromancer or any other evil. My vote is send this orphan back to the forests of Nektulos!&quot; The others gaspsed as Malaehi gathered her strength, and stood up tall. Chanting words to clear her mind and invigorate her body, she is wasted over with a warm aura. <br>
<br>
Lord Kaer, a Koada'dal in the Crimson robe stood up pointing an accusing finger at Mala, &quot;Dare you cast without permission?!&quot; With fire in her eyes, as the Guards approached her, Mala screamed out the same words: &quot;I AM PURE OF HEART AND CHASTE OF BODY. TIS MY SOLE PURPOSE TO SERVE THE GODDESS AND THE CONSUL!&quot; She jerked her hands away as the guards tried to seize her, held her head regally and walked from the room, back into her chambers.<br>
<br>
The Elders were all silent, except for the most Ancient one. A willowy fair Koada'dal femme with unnaturally yellow hair and dark eyebrows, sitting behind the marble table, chuckled softly, &quot;So, the child wants to remain chaste and serve the Goddess, with a spirit like that?&quot; Her body shook with laughter, infectuous laughter at that, soon most of the room was enjoying the joke as well. All but one, who stepped out of the room and out to the balcony to wipe away her tears. The Ancient Kae, a Koada’dal femme with soft features and wide set eyes that stared off into the sunset, whispering a prayer, &quot;Goddess of Love, guide her now, she has been so lost and so forsaken, please give her direction.&quot; Her whispered voice cracks as she pleads, &quot;Be the Mother that should have been there for her&quot;. She crumples to the balcony floor as her image shimmers, illusion falling.<br>
<br>
Still reeling from the day’s events, Mala ran into the confines and security her room where she spent the next two days on her knees praying for guidance. Near the end of the second day, without food, water, Malaehi was deliriously chanting her prayers of meditation. Suddenly, under the crack of the door a warm pink glowing aura drifted in. The room filled with the soothing aura and Mala was lifted off her knees and into the air. She tried to open her eyes but the light was too brilliant, too painful to look at. In the tongue of the Ancients, the messenger of Erollisi Marr whispered words that comforted Malaehi, wiped her tears and giving her instructions. She was refreshed with the blessings of the Goddess, then tucked into her bed. The spirit left as quietly as it had entered as Malaehi drifted off into sleep. In her dreams she was able to understand the message:<br>
<br>
“The Dark and Light Paths must come to know the Love of Erollisi Marr. You will bring this message to all and bear the pain of the messenger. However, I will be with you, my child. Though you will see your death, I will never forsake you. Bear my message child.”<br>
<br>
Malaehi awoke with a start, gathered her things and ran into the Consul’s chambers, unannounced and uninvited. The guards immediately pushed her to the floor and silenced her with a spell. Six of the members of the Ancients were there in conference, and plainly ignored Malaehi’s intrusion. She stayed on the floor kneeled down, not speaking until spoken to for three hours. At last, the ghostly white Mistress Kiae, gazed over with a frown, released the spell of silence, saying: “You troublesome infidel of Malaeliu, why do you vex us?”<br>
<br>
“Hail the Goddess of Love, blessings be upon you all, I have news that is most important..” Malaehi said in a strangled voice.<br>
<br>
Lord Kaer glared at her and snorts: “What would you know of important things, wastrel? Dare you come to the Ancients to school US of importance? Your sniveling voice grates my nerves child of Malaeliu. Silence!” Throwing his hand up, the voice was taken away from Mala again, as tears of frustration streamed down her face. She concentrated hard and sent the telepathic message out to any of the Members who would hear. She recalled the recent events and the spectral visitor last night, and the command she was given. But, they continued to ignore her, and after another five hours they ordered the guards to remove her. Malaehi arrived in her room and stumbled into bed, crying herself to sleep, wondering what she had done. <br>
<br>
In her sleep, one of the Ancients crept into her room and slipped in her bag a note of components of a quest, some provisions and a map book. The Ancient Kae looked upon the sleeping girl, kissed her cheek and whispered: “You will know love as I have known, my ... my child”. Tears trickled down her face as her illusion slipped, revealing the identical features that Malaehi had inherited.<br>
<br>
Malaehi awoke and left Feliwithe bewildered by the harsh treatment, but inspired by the message and purpose she had in her life. She found the note in her bag and ran off to complete her quest, which would give her the gem clustered, golden Rod. She would use this for the rest of her days as an enchantress, to cast a warm glowing aura on all she met, attempting to charm and soften the hearts of all of Norrath. <br>
<br>
...continued...<br>
<br>
&quot;Omnia vincit amor&quot; ~~ &quot;Love conquers all&quot; ~ Erollisi Marr, Goddess of Love<br>
